{
  "texts": [
    "All reviewed studies that used DNN techniques are summarized in Table 2.",
    "To predict at risk students and provide strategies for early intervention in such circumstances, Waheed et al (2019) used five layers of DNNs on a set of special handcrafted features collected from demographic variables and student clickstream activity from VLE.",
    "The effectiveness of the DNN model is divided into four different categories: including distinction-fail, distinction-pass, pass-fail, and withdrawn-pass, with each category classified using binary classification.",
    "The findings demonstrated that the proposed DNN model performed better than the underlying machine learning models, achieving an accuracy of 93%.",
    "Another study by Hussain et al (2019) aimed to predict student outcomes using student's internal assessment data from past semesters."
  ]
}